This PR implements a new trigger tab view. The list of categories/subcategories was replaced with a helper view to give the user a better idea of what triggers to use.
There are several components to this explained below.

### Moving categorized nodes related to computed properties to store

With the new implementation, we're using `categoriesWithNodes`, `visibleNodeTypes` and  `categorizedItems` in several deeply nested components. And because passing them through the props would be tedious, I've moved all of these into the `nodesTypes` store module. We also need to store the main panel's `selectedNodeType` to be able to render category nodes counter in CategoryItem:
```js
nodesCount(): number {
  const currentCategory = this.categoriesWithNodes[this.item.category];
  const subcategories = Object.keys(currentCategory);
  const count = subcategories.reduce((accu: number, subcategory: string) => {
    const countKeys = nodeTypeCountMapper[this.selectedNodeType];
    for (const countKey of countKeys) {
      accu += currentCategory[subcategory][(countKey as "triggerCount" | "regularCount")];
    }
    return accu;
  }, 0);
  return count;
},
```

### Extracting rendering of categories, subcategories and node items into separate component

Because we're now using rendering of these items in two different places, I've moved it into a separate component — [CategorizedItems.vue](https://github.com/n8n-io/n8n/pull/4150/files#diff-7c05df7d6f7a7a6734cee3a646c989379468e021d05e29633c62c0894493f0c6). Additionally this component allows to specify excluded categories and subcategories which will enable us to filter out `OTHER_TRIGGER_NODES_SUBCATEGORY` on `ALL_NODES` tab. And filter out `CORE_NODES_CATEGORY` when showing "App Trigger Nodes" in the new trigger view. 

### Implement the new TriggerHelperPanel

This new component is rendered when the user selects the "Triggers" tab in Node Creator View. It contains a list of `INodeCreateElement` items. I've placed the list into the component's data property since it's only used at this one place, but I'd be happy to move it to a more fitting location(constants?) if somebody has any suggestions. Here when a subcategory is selected, we switch the render from `ItemIterator` to `CategorizedItems` and select the subcategory via $ref of that component.

### NodeCreator scrim
This is something we'll need for [N8N-4641](https://linear.app/n8n/issue/N8N-4641), where we'll show the scrim if the user went to the trigger panel via the new "Choose a Trigger" placeholder node. In this PR, we always show the scrim when the main panel is open to demonstrate it's working as expected. The visibility of the scrim is controlled through the store so that we can trigger it from different components.

